    The role of conidia in long distance dispersal of Didymella rabiei

    The goal of this research is to examine the role of Didymella rabiei conidia on long distance dispersal of chickpea ascochyta blight in Australia.

    Project team

    • Dr Ihsan Khaliq, University of Southern Queensland, Queensland
